 device driver. Maybe it doesn't <br />understand large requests or that the request queue is a linked list and <br />not just one single entry, and the new plug code just changes the way the <br />queue normally looks enough to confuse loop (and md).<br /><br />The plug code is not really new: it's just used in a new way that results <br />in a better layout of the request queue. And it looks like loop and md <br />made some assumptions about how requests can look which aren't true any <br />more.<br /><br />		Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
